    "faq_book_xFYafL": {
      "type": "faq-book",
      "blocks": {
        "item_ATVG9z": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is The Gruffalo about?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p><strong>The Gruffalo</strong> is about a clever mouse who survives a walk through the wood by inventing a monster to scare off hungry animals. The twist is that the monster, the Gruffalo, turns out to be real.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_ih9JRU": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What age is The Gruffalo for?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p><strong>The Gruffalo</strong> is most often enjoyed by children in the early picture-book years, roughly ages 3 to 7, though older children often still enjoy the rhyme, humour and familiar characters.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_mcbcA3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is the main message of The Gruffalo?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p>The story shows that intelligence, confidence and quick thinking can be more powerful than size or strength. Mouse survives because he pays attention, thinks fast and understands how to use a story to protect himself.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_what_is_a_gruffalo": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is a Gruffalo?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p>A Gruffalo is a fictional monster from Julia Donaldson and Axel Scheffler's story. In the book, Mouse first describes the Gruffalo as a made-up creature, then discovers that the creature is real within the world of the story.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_how_many_animals": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How many animals are in The Gruffalo?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p>The story has five main animal or creature characters: Mouse, Fox, Owl, Snake and the Gruffalo. If you are counting only the animals Mouse meets before the Gruffalo, there are three: Fox, Owl and Snake.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_PxWKpf": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Who are the main characters in The Gruffalo?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p>The key characters are <a href=\"/pages/character/mouse\">Mouse</a>, <a href=\"/pages/character/fox\">Fox</a>, Owl, Snake and <a href=\"/pages/character/the-gruffalo\">the Gruffalo</a>. You can also browse the <a href=\"/pages/characters/the-gruffalo\">full Gruffalo character guide</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_when_written": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "When was The Gruffalo written?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p><strong>The Gruffalo</strong> was written by Julia Donaldson, illustrated by Axel Scheffler and first published in 1999.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_look_like": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What does the Gruffalo look like?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p>The Gruffalo is usually shown as a large, horned monster with tusks, claws, orange eyes and purple prickles. His frightening appearance is part of the joke, because Mouse still manages to outwit him.</p>"
          }
        },
        "item_listen": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I listen to The Gruffalo as an audiobook?",
            "check_for_text": "Title",
            "check_for_richtext": "",
            "content": "<p>Yes. You can read the <a href=\"/pages/audiobook/the-gruffalo\">audiobook details</a> or go straight to the <a href=\"/products/the-gruffalo\">The Gruffalo product page</a> to listen on Voxblock.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
